## Battery Impact: Does Fast Charging Hurt Your Battery?

### The Science

- **Level 1 & 2:** Minimal battery degradation, considered "safe" for daily use
- **Level 3 (DC Fast):** Generates more heat, accelerates degradation slightly

### Real-World Impact

**Studies show:**
- EVs fast charged regularly: ~5-10% extra degradation over 100k miles
- Most manufacturers warranty batteries to 70% capacity at 8 years/100k miles
- Daily Level 3 use might reduce this to 65% instead of 70-75%

**Manufacturer Recommendations:**
- Tesla: "Supercharge when needed for long trips"
- Hyundai/Kia: "Limit DC fast charging to preserve battery life"
- Ford: "Use Level 2 for daily charging"

**Bottom Line:** Occasional DC fast charging (road trips, emergencies) is fine. Daily DC fast charging will reduce battery longevity somewhat, but modern batteries are resilient.

