## Tips for Every Charging Level

### Level 1 Tips

1. ✓ Plug in every night without fail (slow recovery needs consistency)
2. ✓ Use a surge protector
3. ✓ Inspect outlet regularly for heat or discoloration
4. ✗ Don't share the circuit with heavy appliances

### Level 2 Tips

1. ✓ Set charge limit to 80% for daily use (extends battery life)
2. ✓ Schedule charging for off-peak hours (lower electricity rates)
3. ✓ Use smart features (scheduling, energy monitoring)
4. ✓ Get a charger with adjustable power (future-proofing)
5. ✗ Don't install yourself (hire licensed electrician)

### Level 3 Tips

1. ✓ Charge to 80%, not 100%, on road trips (faster)
2. ✓ Check PlugShare reviews before relying on a station
3. ✓ Have a backup plan (alternate chargers mapped)
4. ✓ Precondition battery in cold weather (some EVs do this automatically)
5. ✗ Don't use DC fast charging for daily charging (expensive + battery wear)

